WEBVTT

00:06.000 --> 00:12.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

01:04.164 --> 01:05.456
Ruth?

01:15.509 --> 01:16.759
Ruth?

01:46.790 --> 01:48.416
Where's my wife?

01:49.418 --> 01:51.919
Mr. Guttman!
You can't be sneaking up on me like that!

01:52.588 --> 01:54.255
Where is my wife? Where is Ruth?

01:56.258 --> 01:57.884
I'm sorry, Mr. Guttman,

01:59.261 --> 02:01.554
your wife passed away about a week ago.

02:04.641 --> 02:05.808
Ah.

02:17.821 --> 02:19.572
I'm sorry. Who are you?

02:19.698 --> 02:21.532
My name's Paula.

02:21.658 --> 02:23.910
I was Mrs. Guttman's nursing aide.

02:24.661 --> 02:27.246
Your family asked me to stay on
for another week or two.

02:29.333 --> 02:30.583
Let's get some breakfast.

02:31.335 --> 02:33.336
You'll be feeling better after breakfast.

02:33.754 --> 02:35.004
Where are your shoes?

02:35.631 --> 02:37.798
Hold on, let me get you some slippers.
Tell you what.

02:37.925 --> 02:39.634
Trade your hat for some slippers, okay?

02:39.760 --> 02:41.344
All right. Now come in.

02:44.890 --> 02:46.515
- Good morning, Zev.
- Good morning.

02:46.642 --> 02:49.477
I hope you're not too hungry.
Breakfast is crummy as usual.

02:49.603 --> 02:51.395
That's okay. I'm not too hungry.

02:52.522 --> 02:54.857
That's Cele.
She was friends with your wife.

02:54.983 --> 02:57.485
I know who she is. I know who she is.

03:06.495 --> 03:08.371
Could you give us a minute, please?

03:08.705 --> 03:10.748
Oh, no problem...

03:11.625 --> 03:12.583
Max.

03:12.709 --> 03:15.044
You don't have to tell me everyone's name.

03:22.386 --> 03:25.554
Tonight is the last night
sitting shiva for Ruth, yes?

03:27.724 --> 03:30.351
Do you remember what you said you would do

03:31.019 --> 03:32.979
when Ruth died?

03:36.400 --> 03:37.566
No.

03:38.902 --> 03:40.528
It's okay. It's okay.

03:41.822 --> 03:42.905
I...

03:43.657 --> 03:45.032
wrote everything down

03:45.742 --> 03:46.951
so you...

03:47.077 --> 03:48.536
could remember.

03:49.746 --> 03:50.955
(COUGHS)

03:55.919 --> 03:57.294
Come on, Mr. Rosenbaum.

03:57.421 --> 03:59.296
(CONTINUES COUGHING)

03:59.423 --> 04:01.090
(ALL PRAYING)

04:15.480 --> 04:16.647
Darling.

04:17.440 --> 04:19.692
Do you know when this picture was taken?

04:20.944 --> 04:24.405
It's from their wedding day.

04:24.531 --> 04:26.574
1946.

04:27.117 --> 04:29.118
Did you meet nanny in Germany?

04:30.454 --> 04:31.871
Uh, no, no.

04:32.706 --> 04:36.125
I met her in America. I met her...

04:37.002 --> 04:38.461
Coney...

04:39.713 --> 04:41.839
- Coney Island.
- Yeah.

04:42.549 --> 04:44.800
Why don't you show this
to your brother, eh?

04:47.137 --> 04:48.804
Adam, look at this!

04:51.683 --> 04:54.602
Here. Put this away in your pocket.

04:56.521 --> 04:57.605
Now,

04:58.148 --> 04:59.482
stand up.

05:00.609 --> 05:02.068
Tell everyone you're tired,

05:03.653 --> 05:06.822
and go read it alone.

05:07.449 --> 05:08.657
Alone.

05:09.076 --> 05:10.493
You're tired.

05:10.869 --> 05:12.036
Yeah, yeah.

05:12.162 --> 05:13.829
Yeah. Good.

05:20.921 --> 05:22.505
Forgive me, I...

05:22.631 --> 05:26.008
I'm a little tired,
I think I should go to bed.

05:26.134 --> 05:28.135
Yeah. Okay, Dad.

05:29.805 --> 05:31.013
It's been a long week.

05:32.432 --> 05:33.641
Yeah.

06:08.927 --> 06:11.053
(DOOR CREAKING)

06:14.641 --> 06:16.725
(DOOR CLOSING)

06:32.576 --> 06:34.827
- Penn Station, right?
- Yeah.

06:54.139 --> 06:55.514
CONDUCTOR: Last call!

06:55.640 --> 06:57.725
49 Lake Shore Limited!

06:57.851 --> 06:59.226
Last call!

07:00.187 --> 07:03.105
Last call, 49 Lake Shore Limited!

07:03.732 --> 07:05.107
(SIGHING)

07:08.111 --> 07:09.945
Is that your mother?

07:10.655 --> 07:11.822
Yeah.

07:13.200 --> 07:14.700
She's not coming with you?

07:15.952 --> 07:17.786
No. I'm going to see my dad.

07:19.080 --> 07:20.122
Oh.

07:21.625 --> 07:24.084
So, you're traveling all alone?

07:24.211 --> 07:26.962
I'm not alone.
My brothers are right over there.

07:28.632 --> 07:29.757
Oh?

07:30.133 --> 07:31.634
Oh, I see.

07:34.888 --> 07:36.222
Are you going to Cleveland too?

07:36.723 --> 07:37.723
Yeah.

07:37.849 --> 07:39.642
Why don't you fly? It's faster.

07:41.228 --> 07:43.771
I don't know. (CHUCKLES)

07:44.606 --> 07:45.773
That's not a good reason.

07:45.899 --> 07:47.191
(LAUGHING)

07:47.317 --> 07:49.693
You're a real whipper snapper, aren't you?

07:49.819 --> 07:51.153
Why don't you fly to Cleveland?

07:51.905 --> 07:53.656
Three plane tickets is too expensive.

07:54.199 --> 07:55.824
That's what my mom and dad said.

07:56.326 --> 07:58.077
Well, that is a good reason.

07:59.996 --> 08:03.123
I don't fly because
my friend told me to take the train

08:03.250 --> 08:06.752
in the letter he wrote to me.

08:10.215 --> 08:11.924
I guess that's a good reason, too.

08:12.050 --> 08:13.842
- (CHUCKLES)
- My name is Tyler.

08:15.011 --> 08:16.345
Nice to meet you, Tyler.

08:17.180 --> 08:18.806
My name's Zev.

08:19.641 --> 08:20.933
That's a strange name.

08:21.059 --> 08:23.852
In Hebrew, it means "Wolf."

08:23.979 --> 08:26.230
- Cool!
- (LAUGHS)

08:34.072 --> 08:36.365
MAX: I have planned everything for you.

08:37.616 --> 08:40.327
You must follow these steps precisely.

08:41.288 --> 08:44.873
Cross them off as you
accomplish each task.

08:46.960 --> 08:49.378
We've notified the police
and they've issued

08:50.005 --> 08:52.798
a silver alert as well as a reverse 911

08:52.924 --> 08:55.551
to the community, our...
our staff is doing all that we can.

08:55.677 --> 08:57.970
- It's upsetting.
- I just can't believe

08:59.014 --> 09:00.180
this is happening.

09:00.307 --> 09:03.058
I can't tell you how sorry we all are.

09:03.893 --> 09:05.894
We do our best
to keep an eye on everybody,

09:06.021 --> 09:07.855
but... I'm sure you can understand.

09:07.981 --> 09:09.940
WOMAN:
Is there anything we can do to help?

09:10.692 --> 09:12.651
Besides paying you to lose people?

09:13.403 --> 09:15.070
Does your father have a credit card?

09:15.196 --> 09:17.364
You can tell them
to call you if he uses it.

09:18.074 --> 09:19.241
(SCOFFS)

09:21.745 --> 09:22.870
Listen.

09:23.913 --> 09:28.292
Your mother's nursing aid told me that
your dad's been very confused lately.

09:28.418 --> 09:30.794
Yeah, yeah.
That's because he has dementia.

09:30.920 --> 09:33.714
And that's why my mother
brought them here in the first place.

09:33.840 --> 09:37.426
I understand that. However, it's very
common after the death of a spouse

09:37.761 --> 09:40.846
for more signs
of neurocognitive disorders to emerge.

09:42.098 --> 09:44.224
Have you noticed that your father's
been having mood swings?

09:45.435 --> 09:47.936
And he rarely plays the piano anymore?

09:50.023 --> 09:52.900
I've noticed a few things, Charles.

09:55.403 --> 09:56.820
I guess we were...

09:56.946 --> 10:00.282
so busy with your mom
that I just dismissed them.

10:03.036 --> 10:05.788
Let me reassure you,
we'll have him back here before you know it.

10:05.914 --> 10:07.748
In these situations,

10:08.458 --> 10:10.084
people never wander too far.

10:12.712 --> 10:14.129
- (BOTTLES RATTLING)
- (THUD)

10:15.215 --> 10:16.757
Ruth?

10:19.302 --> 10:20.803
Ruth?

10:24.140 --> 10:25.349
Adam?

10:25.475 --> 10:27.267
Where is your grandmother?

10:29.479 --> 10:30.896
Adam?

10:31.022 --> 10:32.439
Where is your grandmother?

10:33.316 --> 10:34.900
Were you talking to me, Zev?

10:35.235 --> 10:37.069
I asked you where your grandmother is.

10:38.488 --> 10:41.281
One is in New York. One is in Ohio.

10:43.868 --> 10:45.202
Where is your sister?

10:46.287 --> 10:47.496
I don't have a sister.

10:49.124 --> 10:50.916
Stop playing with that thing.

10:51.334 --> 10:52.292
Answer me.

10:54.379 --> 10:56.338
Are... are you okay, Zev?

10:58.383 --> 10:59.800
Where are we?

10:59.926 --> 11:01.176
We're on a train.

11:01.970 --> 11:03.262
To where?

11:03.388 --> 11:04.888
Cleveland.

11:06.015 --> 11:07.015
Cleveland?

11:08.268 --> 11:09.977
You're going to see a friend.

11:10.103 --> 11:11.353
What friend?

11:12.480 --> 11:14.940
The one who wrote you
the letter in your pocket.

11:19.279 --> 11:21.113
Can I have my PSP back?

11:40.258 --> 11:42.050
Ruth is dead.

11:48.558 --> 11:50.058
Zev,

11:50.894 --> 11:53.020
I'm going to sit with my brothers
for a little bit.

12:31.601 --> 12:33.268
- Excuse me.
- Yeah?

12:33.394 --> 12:36.063
Hi. Uh... My son there
said that you were sitting

12:36.189 --> 12:38.607
next to him on the train
and that you seemed a little confused.

12:38.942 --> 12:40.776
Oh, yes, that.

12:40.902 --> 12:42.611
- I'm sorry about that.
- Oh, no, no, no.

12:42.946 --> 12:44.404
There's no need to apologize. We...

12:44.989 --> 12:47.741
- just want to make sure you're okay.
- Oh, yes, I'm okay.

12:47.867 --> 12:50.035
Thank you. I'm okay.

12:50.161 --> 12:51.995
Um... You need help getting somewhere?

12:52.121 --> 12:55.082
No, no. Someone will be meeting me here.

12:55.917 --> 12:58.001
My friend said that he had a...

12:58.127 --> 12:59.962
sign with my name on it.

13:00.088 --> 13:02.339
Okay. Well, we'll help you find him.

13:03.967 --> 13:05.217
The cars are just down here.

13:09.889 --> 13:11.139
Is your last name Guttman?

13:11.599 --> 13:12.933
Yeah.

13:13.434 --> 13:14.977
Looks like you're riding in style.

13:16.521 --> 13:18.272
TYLER: Bye, Zev.

13:18.398 --> 13:20.566
Goodbye. Goodbye.

13:21.317 --> 13:22.442
Let's go, boys.

13:22.569 --> 13:24.194
- Mr. Guttman?
- Yeah.

13:25.029 --> 13:26.154
Good.

13:39.294 --> 13:40.669
- Good evening.
- Evening.

13:41.462 --> 13:42.838
How can I help you?

13:42.964 --> 13:46.133
My friend recommended your shop to me.

13:46.509 --> 13:49.011
Well, tell your friend
we appreciate the recommendation.

13:49.137 --> 13:51.305
- What are you looking to pick up?
- Oh...

13:52.015 --> 13:53.682
Something small.

13:55.018 --> 13:55.892
Sure thing. Okay.

13:56.019 --> 13:57.936
- Can I see your driver's license?
- Yeah.

14:06.154 --> 14:07.154
Yeah...

14:08.281 --> 14:09.489
Okay.

14:10.074 --> 14:12.242
Beachwood. Nice town.

14:12.368 --> 14:13.952
Yes. But, um...

14:14.287 --> 14:15.579
We've moved.

14:16.497 --> 14:18.498
We live closer to my son.

14:20.460 --> 14:21.960
What are you doing with my license?

14:22.086 --> 14:26.048
I'm entering your information
into the FBI background check database.

14:26.174 --> 14:27.341
Oh.

14:27.467 --> 14:29.259
What do they look for?

14:29.677 --> 14:31.887
A bunch of stuff.
Whether you're a convicted felon,

14:32.013 --> 14:33.597
if you've been involved
in a crime of violence,

14:33.723 --> 14:35.307
dishonorably discharged from the army,

14:35.433 --> 14:38.393
mentally competent.
If you've got more than one DUI offense

14:38.519 --> 14:40.437
in the last five years,
if you're a fugitive,

14:40.563 --> 14:42.356
- or currently charged with a felony.
- Fugitive?

14:43.316 --> 14:44.941
Yeah, like, if you're
running from the law.

14:45.068 --> 14:47.194
- (CHUCKLES)
- Do I look like I can run?

14:49.238 --> 14:50.489
(CHUCKLES NERVOUSLY)

14:51.449 --> 14:54.242
Uh, okay. Let me show you
some of our smaller handguns.

14:54.369 --> 14:57.371
We got everything.
SIG Sauers, 1911s, Glocks,

14:57.497 --> 14:59.039
single action, double action.

14:59.165 --> 15:01.249
- Sir, do you know much about guns?
- Um...

15:02.460 --> 15:04.628
- No. Why?
- It's all right.

15:04.754 --> 15:06.254
We get all types in here.

15:06.756 --> 15:08.340
Uh, okay. Beginners...

15:09.092 --> 15:10.467
usually go with a .22.

15:10.593 --> 15:12.678
It's light. Easy to use.
Very little recoil.

15:13.721 --> 15:15.263
(MUTTERING)

15:15.390 --> 15:17.641
I think that's what my friend suggested.

15:17.767 --> 15:19.476
Okay. In my opinion,

15:19.602 --> 15:22.521
you might as well get yourself a BB gun
if you get a .22.

15:23.231 --> 15:27.192
Look, I'm not trying
to give you the hard sell, but $500 more,

15:27.318 --> 15:30.404
you can get yourself a gun
with real stopping power.

15:31.489 --> 15:34.658
Now this is a 9mm Glock 17.

15:34.784 --> 15:37.035
Glock? It is German, no?

15:37.161 --> 15:39.579
You're in the right neighborhood.
Manufactured in Austria.

15:40.415 --> 15:43.375
That's the most popular
law enforcement pistol in the world. Okay?

15:43.501 --> 15:45.961
It's got very little recoil
so probably won't hurt your hand

15:46.087 --> 15:47.921
but it'll definitely hurt the intruder.

15:48.047 --> 15:50.590
Is it easy to use?

15:50.717 --> 15:52.175
I hope!

15:52.593 --> 15:53.719
Yeah, it's simple.

15:54.470 --> 15:55.804
Yeah, but...

15:56.139 --> 15:58.265
Would you mind, could you...

15:58.391 --> 16:00.267
write down the instructions for me?

16:02.478 --> 16:05.021
Uh, sure. I mean,
I can show you how to use it.

16:05.148 --> 16:08.817
No, that would be good.
But please, write it down for me.

16:09.819 --> 16:11.528
Sometimes I forget things.

16:17.493 --> 16:21.663
Yeah, we all do, right? That's no problem.

16:21.789 --> 16:23.540
Okay, you're good to go.

16:23.666 --> 16:25.500
I'll grab a pen, and, um...

16:25.626 --> 16:27.461
- write it all down for you.
- (GUN CLICKING)

16:35.094 --> 16:38.388
- Mr. Guttman?
- Guttman. Yeah...

16:38.514 --> 16:39.598
How did you know?

16:39.724 --> 16:42.392
Your friend called earlier
and said you'd be arriving soon.

16:42.518 --> 16:44.227
Your room's all ready for you.

16:44.353 --> 16:46.146
We have you in...

16:46.272 --> 16:49.149
125. Just down the hall.

16:50.610 --> 16:53.612
- How much do I owe?
- It's all taken care of,

16:53.738 --> 16:55.363
including incidentals.

16:56.199 --> 16:59.034
Oh, and I booked your taxi for the morning,
like your friend asked.

16:59.160 --> 17:00.535
Thank you.

17:12.714 --> 17:14.633
(PHONE RINGING)

17:16.676 --> 17:18.553
- Hello?
- Hello.

17:19.430 --> 17:20.763
- Zev?
- Yeah.

17:20.890 --> 17:22.265
It's Max.

17:22.391 --> 17:25.393
I gave the hotel some instructions.

17:26.186 --> 17:29.272
- Are you okay?
- Yes, yes, I'm okay, Max.

17:31.400 --> 17:33.527
And you got the gun?

17:34.403 --> 17:35.695
Yeah, yeah.

17:36.489 --> 17:37.781
Good. Good.

17:38.241 --> 17:40.617
You know what to do.

17:41.911 --> 17:44.579
Just take care of yourself, yeah?

17:45.748 --> 17:48.333
You have a good night, Max.

17:48.459 --> 17:49.751
Good night, Zev.

18:29.292 --> 18:30.667
Ruth?

18:32.253 --> 18:33.461
Ruth?

18:36.465 --> 18:37.883
(BELL DINGS)

18:38.301 --> 18:39.467
Ruth?

18:40.678 --> 18:42.637
Turn on the lights, please.

18:44.348 --> 18:45.974
It's dark in here. I can't...

18:46.684 --> 18:47.976
I can't see.

19:50.831 --> 19:52.040
(PEN CLICKING)

19:59.715 --> 20:01.341
(DOORBELL RINGS)

20:09.892 --> 20:11.601
- Hello.
- Hi.

20:11.727 --> 20:14.604
Is Rudy Kurlander home?

20:14.730 --> 20:16.481
Yeah. He is downstairs.

20:20.695 --> 20:22.654
(MAN LAUGHING)

20:23.823 --> 20:25.657
(VACUUM WHIRRING)

20:26.784 --> 20:28.576
(LAUGHING CONTINUES)

20:35.751 --> 20:38.545
- (TV, INDISTINCT)
- (LAUGHING CONTINUES)

20:52.685 --> 20:54.102
Are you...

20:54.437 --> 20:55.770
Rudy Kurlander?

20:56.605 --> 20:57.647
Yes.

20:57.773 --> 20:59.441
I'm Rudy Kurlander.

20:59.942 --> 21:01.234
Who are you?

21:01.360 --> 21:02.569
Can you, uh...

21:02.945 --> 21:04.070
turn off the television?

21:09.618 --> 21:11.453
- (TURNS OFF TV)
- Do I know you?

21:19.128 --> 21:20.545
Now, please...

21:23.716 --> 21:25.091
stand by the window.

21:26.802 --> 21:27.927
Who are you?

21:29.805 --> 21:31.389
Stand by the window.

21:32.433 --> 21:34.517
I am not going to do anything
until you tell me

21:34.643 --> 21:36.394
who you are and why you're here.

21:37.396 --> 21:38.605
Let us not argue.

21:39.398 --> 21:41.107
Just stand by the window.

22:13.432 --> 22:14.682
Now what?

22:19.647 --> 22:22.482
I need to see light on your face.

22:24.068 --> 22:25.902
- Turn your head.
- Who are you?

22:26.028 --> 22:27.529
Don't yell.

22:27.655 --> 22:28.863
Please, don't yell.

22:30.449 --> 22:32.075
Do as I say. Turn your head.

22:36.205 --> 22:37.664
Are you German?

22:38.207 --> 22:39.207
Yeah.

22:40.501 --> 22:43.002
- (GERMAN) You are also German?
- Ja.

22:44.672 --> 22:45.797
How old are you?

22:46.799 --> 22:48.091
Eighty-eight.

22:49.218 --> 22:51.219
Were you in the German army?

22:52.680 --> 22:54.055
What did you do?

22:54.807 --> 22:57.851
- It is in the past.
- English. Please, English.

22:57.977 --> 23:01.646
- I do not like to speak German.
- It's seventy years ago.

23:01.772 --> 23:03.106
I was very young.

23:03.232 --> 23:04.732
Answer the question.

23:07.194 --> 23:08.695
Are you a Jew?

23:10.072 --> 23:11.156
Yeah.

23:12.074 --> 23:14.242
- Were you at Auschwitz?
- No!

23:15.244 --> 23:16.995
We are too old for lies.

23:19.540 --> 23:21.708
I didn't know about Auschwitz

23:22.585 --> 23:24.252
until after the war.

23:24.587 --> 23:26.171
I was in North Africa.

23:27.590 --> 23:29.132
With General Rommel.

23:32.094 --> 23:34.095
- You have proof?
- Yes.

23:35.639 --> 23:37.056
Over there.

23:46.108 --> 23:50.111
When I became a US citizen,
the immigration officer asked me

23:51.197 --> 23:53.573
if I had ever associated

23:53.699 --> 23:55.909
with the Nazi government of Germany

23:56.035 --> 23:59.037
or worked at a concentration camp.

24:01.123 --> 24:03.625
I told the officer what I'll tell you.

24:05.044 --> 24:07.962
Yes, I served for my country.
I was a soldier.

24:08.881 --> 24:11.299
I was a proud German
and that's what the men did.

24:12.635 --> 24:15.303
I'm still proud of my service.

24:22.895 --> 24:24.229
That's Rommel.

24:26.857 --> 24:28.650
As far as the Jews...

24:32.696 --> 24:36.241
I didn't care about the Jews.
I thought Hitler was right.

24:37.868 --> 24:40.328
They caused many problems for the country.

24:41.580 --> 24:46.125
I thought we were deporting them
or putting them in work camps...

24:47.253 --> 24:48.753
Not what they did.

24:52.216 --> 24:53.716
It was shameful,

24:54.635 --> 24:56.010
but that was not me.

25:00.349 --> 25:01.808
(PHONE RINGING)

25:09.024 --> 25:12.151
- Hello?
- Is this Max?

25:13.028 --> 25:14.070
Yes.

25:14.738 --> 25:15.989
This is Zev.

25:16.115 --> 25:17.740
Uh... It was...

25:18.325 --> 25:19.367
not him.

25:20.953 --> 25:24.038
- Are you sure?
- Yeah, I'm sure.

25:25.624 --> 25:26.958
Then you must go on.

25:27.835 --> 25:29.294
You must do

25:30.296 --> 25:31.963
what you said you would.

25:47.104 --> 25:49.105
There have been rumors for years

25:49.231 --> 25:53.109
that a number of Auschwitz SS officers

25:53.235 --> 25:57.071
stole the identities of executed prisoners

25:57.197 --> 25:58.906
near the end of the war.

25:59.867 --> 26:02.618
Shortly after my stroke,

26:02.745 --> 26:06.164
evidence was found
that an Auschwitz Blockführer

26:06.874 --> 26:10.293
emigrated from Germany in the 1940s

26:10.419 --> 26:14.255
and was most likely living under the name

26:14.381 --> 26:16.674
Rudy Kurlander.

26:17.301 --> 26:19.594
The Simon Wiesenthal Center

26:19.720 --> 26:22.930
has found four Rudy Kurlanders

26:23.057 --> 26:25.350
who emigrated during that period.

26:26.143 --> 26:28.644
However, there is not enough proof

26:28.771 --> 26:30.688
to arrest any of them.

26:34.109 --> 26:38.446
His real name is Otto Wallisch.

26:40.824 --> 26:43.868
You must find him.

26:48.832 --> 26:52.460
CHARLES: I'm looking for my father.
He's almost 90 years old.

26:53.962 --> 26:56.172
His name is Zev.

26:56.298 --> 26:57.882
I'm looking for my father.

26:58.467 --> 27:00.009
He's 90 years old.

27:00.135 --> 27:02.845
He went wandering a few days ago.

27:03.180 --> 27:05.640
His name is Zev Guttman.

27:05.766 --> 27:08.976
I don't know if he has
any identification on him,

27:09.103 --> 27:11.938
or... I don't even know
if he remembers his name.

27:12.064 --> 27:15.400
I've been wondering if anybody
has been brought into the hospital.

27:17.986 --> 27:21.155
Do you not think
I've already called the police?

27:28.247 --> 27:31.374
PA: Ladies and gentlemen,
we're approaching the Canadian border,

27:31.500 --> 27:34.627
at which point, we're all gonna have
to get off the bus for inspection.

27:34.753 --> 27:37.046
If you can have your passports
and any travel documents ready,

27:37.172 --> 27:40.091
it'll make the process a lot faster.
Thank you.

27:56.400 --> 27:58.484
(DOG PANTING)

28:00.529 --> 28:01.946
(DOG GROWLS)

28:03.866 --> 28:05.032
Declaration card?

28:07.369 --> 28:08.911
Purpose of your trip?

28:09.037 --> 28:11.539
To see a friend.

28:11.874 --> 28:12.832
What's your friend's name?

28:12.958 --> 28:15.042
- Rudy Kurlander.
- Where does he live?

28:15.169 --> 28:18.546
Foyer Des... Foyer...

28:25.220 --> 28:27.346
- Can I see that?
- Yeah, of course.

28:29.558 --> 28:32.351
- Foyer Des Pionniers Nursing Home?
- Yeah.

28:32.478 --> 28:34.770
And you'll be staying
at the Queen's Motel in Hearst, Ontario?

28:34.897 --> 28:35.897
That's right.

28:36.273 --> 28:37.565
How long will you be in Canada?

28:38.233 --> 28:40.902
Two nights. Maybe.

28:42.070 --> 28:43.279
Passport?

29:02.424 --> 29:04.050
Sir, your passport's expired.

29:05.469 --> 29:07.220
- It is?
- Yeah.

29:10.432 --> 29:12.141
Do you have a driver's license?

29:12.267 --> 29:14.018
Oh, of course.

29:19.024 --> 29:20.233
Hang on a second.

29:38.001 --> 29:39.418
Alright, you're good to go.

29:40.128 --> 29:41.379
But, sir, renew your passport.

29:41.505 --> 29:43.214
(ZEV CHUCKLES)

29:43.340 --> 29:46.259
I didn't think it was necessary at my age.

29:48.011 --> 29:49.136
Have fun with your friend.

29:49.263 --> 29:50.638
Thank you.

30:24.506 --> 30:25.798
Excuse me.

30:25.924 --> 30:27.008
How can I help you, sir?

30:27.134 --> 30:30.678
Rudy Kurlander. Which room is he in?

30:31.013 --> 30:32.513
Kurlander?

30:32.639 --> 30:35.016
Yes, Kurlander. He's in room 238.

30:35.142 --> 30:38.269
Just go down this hallway
and take the elevators.

30:38.395 --> 30:42.023
When you exit the elevator,
make a left, then you take a right.

30:42.149 --> 30:44.066
238 will be on your left.

30:45.360 --> 30:46.694
Did you get that?

30:47.946 --> 30:50.072
Why don't I just show you
where your friend's room is?

30:50.198 --> 30:51.198
Thank you.

31:18.977 --> 31:20.394
(ZEV CLEARS THROAT) Uh...

31:20.520 --> 31:22.563
Are you Rudy Kurlander?

31:25.108 --> 31:26.859
Rudy Kurlander?

31:26.985 --> 31:28.235
Here.

31:54.471 --> 31:58.099
- Are you Rudy Kurlander?
- Yeah.

32:01.144 --> 32:02.311
Are you German?

32:03.105 --> 32:04.146
Yes.

32:07.609 --> 32:10.569
Were you at Auschwitz?

32:14.241 --> 32:15.449
Yes.

32:19.329 --> 32:22.123
I was at Auschwitz.

32:24.251 --> 32:27.253
My whole family was

32:28.797 --> 32:30.339
murdered

32:31.049 --> 32:32.508
at Auschwitz.

32:35.137 --> 32:36.595
I'm so sorry.

32:38.557 --> 32:40.266
You're... you're sorry?

32:42.060 --> 32:43.394
Yeah.

32:46.398 --> 32:51.527
What you did is something
you cannot apologize for.

32:56.324 --> 32:59.160
I swore I would kill the man responsible

32:59.286 --> 33:01.120
for the death of my family.

33:11.673 --> 33:13.424
You're Jewish?

33:14.217 --> 33:15.593
Homosexual.

33:21.266 --> 33:23.309
It is I who am sorry.

33:28.315 --> 33:32.193
I'm sorry. I'm so sorry! (SOBBING)

34:14.735 --> 34:17.655
(PIANO PLAYING)

34:51.648 --> 34:53.232
Moszkowski.

34:54.275 --> 34:55.943
You know Moszkowski?

34:56.277 --> 34:59.113
My old piano teacher used to say

34:59.239 --> 35:01.782
that the three greatest composers

35:02.617 --> 35:04.869
were Mendelssohn, Meyerbeer

35:05.453 --> 35:06.704
and Moszkowski.

35:07.289 --> 35:09.957
- Do you still play?
- Oh...

35:10.625 --> 35:12.334
(CHUCKLES) No.

35:12.460 --> 35:14.545
No, I don't know, I'm not sure!

35:14.671 --> 35:15.796
Well...

35:16.798 --> 35:19.758
Why don't you give it a try?

35:20.552 --> 35:22.386
Oh... Well...

35:23.680 --> 35:24.930
(EXHALES)

35:25.974 --> 35:27.266
Mendelssohn.

35:27.642 --> 35:28.851
Maybe. (CHUCKLES)

35:32.314 --> 35:34.690
(PIANO, HUMMING)

36:11.853 --> 36:13.854
(PIANO MUSIC CONTINUES)

37:09.661 --> 37:10.661
(ELEVATOR BELL DINGS)

37:13.873 --> 37:16.000
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

37:17.085 --> 37:19.420
Hello, sir. Welcome to Boise.

37:20.714 --> 37:22.089
Do you have a reservation?

37:22.507 --> 37:25.467
(MUFFLED) I have a note that
you need a taxi pickup at 8:00 am.

37:25.593 --> 37:30.597
So, we have our complimentary breakfast
which starts at 6:00 a.m.

37:32.726 --> 37:35.811
And if you just head through
the lobby to your left...

37:43.111 --> 37:44.653
Here, let me help you, okay?

37:50.952 --> 37:51.869
(STUTTERS)

37:51.995 --> 37:55.497
There is one thing.
I forgot to pack more clothes.

37:55.623 --> 37:56.999
- Extra clothes.
- Oh!

37:57.125 --> 37:59.626
We can definitely help you out with that.

37:59.753 --> 38:02.504
So, there's a downtown shuttle
that leaves every hour on the hour

38:02.630 --> 38:06.383
and it's going to drop you right off
at the mall on North Milwaukee street.

38:07.594 --> 38:09.803
(MUFFLED) You should be able to get
everything you need there...

38:15.685 --> 38:18.771
Sir, would you like me to do that?

38:19.606 --> 38:20.814
Sir, are you okay?

38:23.109 --> 38:26.403
Would you like to head up
to your room now? Okay.

38:40.627 --> 38:42.795
- Can I help you find anything?
- Oh, yes.

38:42.921 --> 38:45.172
I want to buy a new shirt.

38:45.965 --> 38:48.008
We have a great deal
on short-sleeve button downs.

38:48.134 --> 38:49.051
- Yeah?
- Can I show you?

38:49.511 --> 38:51.053
- Thank you.
- Yeah.

38:51.179 --> 38:53.305
You can always find the best deals
at the end of the season.

38:53.431 --> 38:54.848
Oh, right.

38:59.020 --> 39:00.979
(ALARM BLARING)

39:03.900 --> 39:06.068
Excuse me, sir. You set off the alarm.

39:06.194 --> 39:07.903
I'm gonna have to check your bag.

39:08.029 --> 39:09.947
Oh. Do I look like a thief?

39:10.448 --> 39:12.699
Oh, it doesn't matter, sir,
you set off the alarm.

39:12.826 --> 39:14.993
I've got to check your bag
no matter what, so...

39:15.120 --> 39:16.120
There's the receipt.

39:17.455 --> 39:18.705
Oh, there's your problem right there.

39:19.040 --> 39:20.707
They left the security tag on.

39:21.209 --> 39:23.043
I'll have to check
your other bag too, sir.

39:35.056 --> 39:36.056
Is that a Glock?

39:37.100 --> 39:38.100
Yeah.

39:41.187 --> 39:43.939
(CHUCKLES) Reminds me of my first gun.

39:44.899 --> 39:46.525
- (BAG ZIPPING)
- You have a good day, sir.

39:46.651 --> 39:50.946
- There you go. Thanks very much.
- Thank you. Thank you...

40:01.499 --> 40:02.791
(ELEVATOR BELL DINGS)

40:07.046 --> 40:08.213
(SCATTERED APPLAUSE)

40:09.507 --> 40:11.091
(COUGHING)

40:14.762 --> 40:16.597
(BREATHING SHAKILY)

40:41.789 --> 40:43.290
(COUGHING)

40:46.669 --> 40:48.420
WOMAN: Would you like a refill?

40:48.546 --> 40:50.422
- Yes. Thank you.
- You're very welcome.

40:50.548 --> 40:51.673
(CHILDREN SCREAMING)

40:51.799 --> 40:54.635
Could you tell me how far
is Bruneau is from here?

40:54.761 --> 40:57.679
I've never actually been to Bruneau,
but it's in Owyhee County,

40:57.805 --> 41:00.641
so, I'd say that should probably take you
about 30, 40 minutes or so.

41:00.767 --> 41:02.893
- Oh.
- I heard it's beautiful country down there.

41:03.019 --> 41:04.561
- I never get to go but my friends...
- (CHILDREN SCREAMING)

41:04.687 --> 41:05.812
- Oh!
- Ah.

41:05.939 --> 41:07.105
Oh, I'm so sorry!

41:07.232 --> 41:09.024
- I got coffee on your letter.
- Oh, God.

41:09.150 --> 41:10.108
No, you're ruining my letter!

41:10.235 --> 41:12.027
- No, no, no!
- I'm sorry.

41:12.153 --> 41:15.656
This letter is very important!
Stop! Stop! Stop!

41:15.990 --> 41:18.033
(HAIR DRYER WHIRRING)

41:22.288 --> 41:25.082
"Besides me,

41:25.208 --> 41:29.294
"you are the only person

41:31.172 --> 41:35.008
"who can still recognize

41:38.054 --> 41:41.974
"the face of the man

41:42.892 --> 41:48.313
"who murdered our families."

42:20.972 --> 42:23.056
(DOG BARKING)

42:28.896 --> 42:31.356
- (KNOCKING ON DOOR)
- (DOG CONTINUES BARKING)

42:37.739 --> 42:39.406
- Nobody's home?
- No.

42:39.866 --> 42:41.283
You want me to take you somewhere else?

42:41.659 --> 42:44.202
- No, no, no. I will wait.
- Here.

42:46.414 --> 42:49.249
Give me a call whenever you want me
to come back and get you.

42:49.917 --> 42:51.335
What do I owe you?

42:52.086 --> 42:54.171
Oh, you already paid me, remember?

42:56.424 --> 42:58.300
Just call me if you need a ride later.

43:03.014 --> 43:05.223
(SIREN WAILING IN DISTANCE)

43:07.435 --> 43:09.144
(EXPLOSION)

43:45.306 --> 43:46.973
(DOG BARKING)

43:48.976 --> 43:49.976
Morning.

43:53.356 --> 43:55.899
- Morning to you too, sweetie.
- (DOG CONTINUES BARKING)

44:06.828 --> 44:07.828
Yeah...

44:11.499 --> 44:12.999
Dinner time, Mr. Rosenbaum.

44:14.335 --> 44:15.335
Uh...

44:15.837 --> 44:17.337
Bring me back some food, yeah?

44:18.840 --> 44:21.049
Are you sure? You haven't been
outside the apartment all day.

44:21.175 --> 44:23.844
- Yes.
- Okay.

44:25.221 --> 44:26.221
(SIGHS)

44:55.001 --> 44:56.334
Can I help you with something?

44:57.170 --> 45:00.005
I'm looking for Rudy Kurlander.

45:04.051 --> 45:06.219
Well, you came
to the right place but, uh...

45:09.265 --> 45:11.808
My old man passed away
about three months ago.

45:12.810 --> 45:15.562
Oh, I didn't know this. I am so sorry.

45:17.899 --> 45:18.899
Hmm...

45:23.571 --> 45:25.071
How long have you been waiting here?

45:26.574 --> 45:27.574
All day.

45:31.078 --> 45:32.287
You want a drink?

45:34.373 --> 45:35.540
A drink would be nice.

45:36.918 --> 45:37.876
Come on in.

45:38.002 --> 45:40.253
I could use another drink myself.
(CHUCKLES)

45:40.379 --> 45:42.881
- Thank you.
- Beer or a water?

45:43.007 --> 45:45.217
Just water, please.

45:48.429 --> 45:50.972
Oh, Eva. Good girl. Good girl.

45:52.892 --> 45:54.601
Listen, I am a little scared of dogs.

45:55.019 --> 45:56.603
Eva's all bark and no bite. Come on in.

45:56.979 --> 46:00.440
But I'm sure that's true
but I'm... I'm quite scared.

46:00.566 --> 46:02.400
Oh, I'll put her away for you. Okay.

46:02.944 --> 46:04.736
Here we go. Good girl.

46:04.862 --> 46:06.112
Quiet, girl. Eva!

46:06.239 --> 46:07.864
Eva, shush, quiet.

46:07.990 --> 46:10.951
(SHUSHING)
Girl, quiet. Calm down, Eva. Shush.

46:11.619 --> 46:13.453
Eva, shush. Shush.

46:13.579 --> 46:16.081
Eva, calm down now. Calm down.

46:18.626 --> 46:21.127
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

46:21.504 --> 46:23.088
- Quiet!
- (DOOR CLOSING)

46:32.223 --> 46:34.099
- (SIGHS)
- (EXPLOSION)

46:39.647 --> 46:42.482
That's my, um, kid's graduation.

46:43.985 --> 46:45.360
Dad always loved that photo.

46:46.153 --> 46:48.280
- I'm gonna get... grab your water for you.
- Yeah.

46:48.656 --> 46:51.032
When was that taken?
Your father looks so young.

46:51.158 --> 46:53.618
That was, uh, in 1997.

46:54.620 --> 46:57.998
- Oh.
- Yeah. Dad aged well, didn't he?

46:58.124 --> 46:59.332
1997.

46:59.917 --> 47:04.129
He always said that he was
one of the Kurlanders with good genes.

47:05.590 --> 47:06.590
Here you go.

47:13.014 --> 47:13.972
(ZEV SIGHING)

47:14.098 --> 47:16.391
Oh, you were thirstier than Eva.
(CHUCKLES)

47:17.685 --> 47:19.352
- Another one?
- Oh, please.

47:19.687 --> 47:21.563
And then I won't bother you again.

47:21.689 --> 47:24.024
Oh, no, no. It's no bother at all.

47:24.942 --> 47:26.359
Stay as long as you like.

47:27.570 --> 47:31.197
Ever since, uh... since Dad died,
it's been pretty lonely out here.

47:33.534 --> 47:36.036
You know, I'm just driving around

47:36.370 --> 47:41.291
doing my rounds, with nothing but the radio
and the occasional dispatch.

47:41.417 --> 47:42.375
(DOG BARKING)

47:42.501 --> 47:45.211
It's good to have someone to talk to
when I come home.

47:46.047 --> 47:48.214
Eva's great and all,
but not much for conversation.

47:48.674 --> 47:51.051
- Here's your water.
- You're not married?

47:51.177 --> 47:54.179
No, no. Have a seat.
I was, you know, twice.

47:55.097 --> 47:57.432
The first one, uh, took my house,

47:58.392 --> 48:00.101
the second one left before...

48:00.227 --> 48:02.062
(SIGHS) ...the quarry takes this one.

48:02.188 --> 48:03.146
(LAUGHING)

48:03.272 --> 48:06.358
That was...
Ooh, hell, seven years already.

48:07.276 --> 48:08.693
I wouldn't mind getting another one,

48:09.403 --> 48:12.530
but Bruneau ain't exactly
the best singles scene

48:13.574 --> 48:16.326
and, well, I ain't exactly the best single.
(CHUCKLING)

48:18.996 --> 48:23.333
Did your father ever talk to you
about Germany?

48:24.585 --> 48:25.752
Are you kidding me?

48:26.379 --> 48:28.088
He never stopped talking about Germany.

48:29.507 --> 48:31.424
Did he ever speak to you about the war?

48:32.009 --> 48:33.009
Of course.

48:33.678 --> 48:35.178
You know he was a collector, right?

48:35.763 --> 48:36.763
Ah.

48:38.641 --> 48:41.309
I got a bunch of his stuff.
You wanna go take a look?

48:42.269 --> 48:43.269
Yeah.

48:44.105 --> 48:45.772
Watch your step. Just come down here.

48:46.607 --> 48:47.524
(CLEARS THROAT)

48:47.650 --> 48:48.650
- (SIRENS WAILING IN DISTANCE)
- (EXPLOSION)

48:50.111 --> 48:52.779
- (DOG BARKING)
- (SHUSHING)

48:54.448 --> 48:56.616
Eva, quiet! Eva, shh.

48:56.742 --> 49:00.328
Hey, listen, uh,
it's kind of a mess in here.

49:00.454 --> 49:02.247
Let me just move some boxes and I'll...

49:02.707 --> 49:05.125
I'll let you in the other room.

49:05.251 --> 49:08.086
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

49:08.212 --> 49:09.212
(GRUNTS)

49:10.297 --> 49:11.297
Here we go.

49:12.425 --> 49:14.592
There we go. There. Come on. Oh!

49:16.804 --> 49:17.804
Come on in.

49:24.311 --> 49:27.772
That was, uh...
that was Dad's pride and joy.

49:29.400 --> 49:36.156
The dealer he bought it from swore
it was flying in Berlin on November 19, 1938.

49:37.283 --> 49:38.533
Kristallnacht.

49:39.660 --> 49:41.286
Kristallnacht... Yeah.

49:43.664 --> 49:46.708
Dad used to say that that flag, um,

49:47.293 --> 49:50.837
witnessed the beginning of history.

49:52.339 --> 49:53.339
You know?

49:59.180 --> 50:01.723
- What is in these boxes?
- Uh, just...

50:02.683 --> 50:05.727
a bunch more of Dad's prize pieces.
You know?

50:05.853 --> 50:08.188
I already sold most of the collection

50:08.314 --> 50:13.693
but, uh, these are the things
he was sentimental about.

50:15.696 --> 50:19.449
Just haven't been able
to let myself get rid of 'em, you know?

50:23.746 --> 50:25.455
You wanna look around?
You wanna look around?

50:25.581 --> 50:27.207
- Thank you.
- Yeah.

50:42.723 --> 50:44.307
Yeah, that was a first printing.

50:45.226 --> 50:48.645
A guy offered me six grand for it
but I just... just couldn't part with it.

50:51.232 --> 50:53.399
I guess I'm just as sentimental
as my old man, huh?

50:53.526 --> 50:54.526
(CHUCKLES)

50:56.862 --> 51:00.323
You're welcome to look around
at... at anything you like.

51:00.908 --> 51:02.742
I'm just gonna give Eva her dinner.

51:18.425 --> 51:19.425
(EVA BARKING)

51:22.596 --> 51:23.596
Quiet! Shh!

51:39.613 --> 51:40.905
Priceless, right?

51:43.367 --> 51:44.367
Yeah.

51:45.536 --> 51:48.746
I guess I shouldn't leave it
stuffed in a box like that.

51:52.877 --> 51:53.877
(SNIFFLING)

52:00.509 --> 52:02.552
(SIGHING)

52:04.305 --> 52:05.430
You want another drink?

52:06.223 --> 52:07.473
Yes. That would be good.

52:08.809 --> 52:11.811
More water, or something
a little stronger?

52:12.605 --> 52:14.981
Maybe something a little stronger.

52:15.482 --> 52:16.482
All right.

52:17.484 --> 52:19.402
Now you're speaking my language.
(CHUCKLES)

52:19.820 --> 52:20.820
Yeah...

52:25.910 --> 52:27.577
To Dad.

52:28.746 --> 52:30.246
(GLASSES TINKLING)

52:33.542 --> 52:35.001
You know, my dad was, uh...

52:36.337 --> 52:37.545
My dad was there that night.

52:38.339 --> 52:40.882
- What night was that?
- Um, Kristal...

52:41.008 --> 52:42.800
- Kristallnacht.
- Yeah. Kristallnacht.

52:43.594 --> 52:45.637
Yeah, he said he had a hammer

52:46.263 --> 52:48.431
and he broke a bunch
of jewelry store windows.

52:48.557 --> 52:50.475
- He ever tell you that story?
- No.

52:50.601 --> 52:51.684
No? (CHUCKLES)

52:52.478 --> 52:54.604
I so wish you were here
when he was still alive.

52:54.730 --> 52:58.149
You know, every once in a while,
some of his buddies would come by

52:58.275 --> 53:01.736
and they'd just sit around,
tell stories, drink, you know?

53:02.696 --> 53:05.490
He loved to talk about the old days.

53:07.326 --> 53:08.952
You okay? You're sweating there.

